//StringsFromMaps
"OutdoorString0": "A marble statue depiciting a conventionally attractive woman. You wonder if it reflects the owner's tastes.",
"OutdoorString1": "PEI MING",
"OutdoorString2": "Pei Ming seems to have locked the door for you and doesn't want you to enter his house anymore.",

"PeiMingHouse.000": "You wish you had never seen what's inside that drawer.",
"PeiMingHouse.001": "Those look like strategic notes... or, wait? Is that a... poem?",
"PeiMingHouse.002": "You wonder why Pei Ming has a kitchen at all. He can neither cook nor does he like doing it, but expects women to be perfect cooks. Perhaps you should teach him a lesson someday.",
"PeiMingHouse.003": "Pei Ming seems to be fond of roses.",
"PeiMingHouse.004": "A good book and tea gets you through the gloomiest day. Even Pei Ming seems to understand that. You check the book cover and read the title 'Heaven Official's Blessing'.",
"PeiMingHouse.005": "An interesting collection of trinkets and artifacts that seem as if they were from a whole different world. It appears that they manifested here just as randomly as Pei Ming did.",
"PeiMingHouse.006": "Pei Ming appears to enjoy wine. This bottle looks very expensive...",
"PeiMingHouse.007": "Different kinds of robes that are befitting of an ancient deity. Pei Ming really sticks out like a sore thumb here.",
"PeiMingHouse.008": "Fresh and cheap?... there is something written in the bottom left corner of the flag. 'Happy birthday from your two best friends, old Pei.'",
"PeiMingHouse.009": "You always find a freshly brewed mug of tea here. You would never find him drink tea from those cheap tea bags.",

"PeiMingSpouseRoom.000": "Pei Ming deposited books of all genres for indoor days here.",
"PeiMingSpouseRoom.001": "Since Pei Ming loves roses so much, he put some on display here.",
"PeiMingSpouseRoom.002": "Pei Ming's favorite wine. Maybe you should have a drink with him together later.",


//roommate schedule dialogue (after he moved in)
"PMRoommate0": "Ah, good morning, @. Do you want to head to the Night Market together later?",
"PMRoommate1": "I thought it would be nice to have a little drink before heading to the Night Market. Why don't you have some, too?#$b# Don't worry, I'll pay!$1 [(O)873 (O)903 (O)Wildflour.AtelierGoods_Bonfire_Ale (O)Wildflour.AtelierGoods_Snowman_Cream_Ale (O)Wildflour.AtelierGoods_Sunny_Daze_Mead]",
"PMRoommate2": "@! You actually came to the Night Market!$1#$e# I am pretty curious about the vendors that have set up shop here.",
"PMRoommate3": "So there are even real mermaids, huh? #$e# Perhaps I'll check them out. $3",
"PMRoommate4": "Ah, so you've decided to hike up the mountain, too? I quite enjoyed myself doing so.$6",
"PMRoommate5": "A 'witch' lives in here, according to rumors. I sort of want to check out this place.",
"PMRoommate6": "During Winter, I prefer retreating to my abode and enjoy some tea just how I like it. #$e# You are always free to join, naturally.",
"PMRoommate7": "Missing me on the farm already? $3#$e# Worry not! I shall return shortly.$6",

//Movies

"MovieInvitation": "Movies? This is the modern form of stageplay, no? Well, I am all for it. $1",
"RejectMovieTicket_AlreadyInvitedBySomeoneElse": "Too bad, somebody else has already invited me.",
"RejectMovieTicket_AlreadyWatchedThisWeek": "I have already watched a movie this week. Why don't we go next week?",
"RejectMovieTicket_Divorced": "Are you serious? $7",
"RejectMovieTicket_DontWantToSeeThatMovie": "I don't find this movie interesting enough. Why don't you ask someone else? #$b# Or just don't go and the two of us go grab a drink instead? $3",
"RejectMovieTicket": "I have other things to do. Like... #$b# %Pei Ming pretends to think for a long time. #$b# Like........ Staring at the sea.",

"Movies.0": "So you are telling me the actors in this movie are not real but drawn by artist? What a strange idea...",
"Movies.1": "%Pei Ming appears to be bored.",
"Movies.2": "That wasn't really what I hoped for. Too bad, but I did enjoy the time with a friend.",
"Movies.3": "I heard this is based on a so-called 'video game'. What is that?",
"Movies.4": "Woah!",
"Movies.5": "I did not really understand the story but I had lots of fun anyway. $6",
"Movies.6": "I don't know what to think of this movie. 'Mysterium'? This entire world is a mysterium. Hoho!",
"Movies.7": "Hm... a little scary, no?",
"Movies.8": "I have to be honest: I am not too fond of scary movies. #$b# But since you were around, I had fun. $6",
"Movies.9": "Thank you for the invitation during those cold Winter days. #$b# I think it's fun to go to this place together!",
"Movies.10": "Huh?!$8#$b# When did I fall asleep? Why didn't you wake me up?$8#$b# Haha, please forigve this venerable one. I did not like the story at all.",
"Movies.11": "Oh, so this is an informational piece, you say? #$b# Sounds great! That way, I can learn even more about this area. $6#$b# I didn't think there would be things like that in this time and age.",
"Movies.12": "Now that was interesting. I learned so much! #$b# I can't believe that the vegetation in this valley is...#$b#%Pei Ming continues to yap about the documentary for another 30 minutes.",
"Movies.13": "'It howls in the rain'... Do you think it's got anything to do with wolves? #$b# I find wolves quite interesting.$1",
"Movies.14": "Are they stupid?",
"Movies.15": "With all due respect, these children were acting like buffoons. #$b# Perhaps they should train under me to learn some rational thinking. $9",
"Movies.16": "So you say that this is considered a classic these days? #$b# Well, to me, it is still quite the novelty!$1",
"Movies.17": "No... it can't be...",
"Movies.18": "I see why this is considered a 'classic'. It was really good! #$b# And the actress was...#$b# ... you know.< $3",

}